I"À<h3 id="instance">Instance</h3>

<ul>
  <li>In C++ object live in the memory where are they are instantiated.</li>
  <li>In Java the objects are allocated in heap memory. The reference to the allocated heap memory is stored as value on the stack. The object in the heap memory contains a table with <strong>vptr</strong> that points to the functions in the static memory.</li>
</ul>
